    "The self-assessment reveals several patterns across the team:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Statistical Analysis** is the team's relative strength, with an average score of **2.75**, reflecting shared exposure through academic coursework.\n",
    "- **SQL** follows closely at **2.50**, suggesting moderate but uneven proficiency — useful for basic queries, but likely insufficient for complex analytical workflows.\n",
    "- **Git/GitHub** stands out as the most uniformly weak skill, with every member rating themselves at **1 or 2**. This is a critical gap given that version control is foundational to any collaborative data project.\n",
    "- **Machine Learning** and **Cloud Computing** are also low across the board, with three out of four members rating themselves at **1** — indicating limited hands-on experience beyond introductory exposure.\n",
    "\n",
