    "### Key Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "The market data tells a clear story: **Python and SQL are non-negotiable baselines** for data roles, appearing in 95% and 88% of postings respectively. Together, they form the minimum entry bar for most positions.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Machine Learning (75%)** ranks third — higher than many candidates might expect — reflecting the growing expectation that even non-specialist data analysts should be familiar with ML concepts and tools. **Cloud Computing (65%)** has surged in demand as enterprise workflows migrate to AWS, Azure, and GCP.\n",
    "\n",
    "Notably, **R (45%)**, though still valued in academic and research contexts, ranks last among the seven skills — suggesting that for industry roles, Python-first fluency is far more marketable.\n",
    "\n",
