    "### Findings\n",
    "\n",
    "The gap analysis highlights three tiers of urgency:\n",
    "\n",
    "**🔴 High Priority (Gap > 1.5)**\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Python** — Team average of 2.5 vs. market demand of 4.75. This is the single most critical gap. Python is required in nearly every data role, and the team's current level is insufficient for professional-level work.\n",
    "- **Machine Learning** — Team average of 1.75 vs. market demand of 3.75. Most team members have minimal hands-on experience, yet ML fluency is increasingly expected even in analyst-level roles.\n",
    "- **Cloud Computing** — Team average of 1.5 vs. market demand of 3.25. While less universally required, cloud proficiency is becoming a table-stakes expectation in enterprise environments.\n",
    "\n",
    "**🟡 Medium Priority (Gap 0.5–1.5)**\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Git/GitHub** — The gap is moderate numerically, but the skill's foundational nature makes it practically more urgent. Collaborative work in any technical role depends on version control.\n",
    "- **R** — A smaller gap, but largely because market demand for R is also lower relative to Python.\n",
    "\n",
    "**🟢 Low Priority (Gap < 0.5)**\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Statistical Analysis** and **SQL** — The team performs relatively close to market expectations. These are areas to maintain and deepen rather than urgently build from scratch.\n",
